  <tr>
    <td class="table-bold">Dividend Policy</td>
    <td class="table" colspan="4">
      The Company has a policy to pay dividends at the rate of not less than 40 percent of the net profit after deducting corporate income tax and legal reserve that shall be significantly considered based on the Company&#039;s separate financial statement. However, the Board of Directors of the Company shall have an authority to waive the compliance abiding by such policy or amend such policy from time to time in case such undertaking shall cause the greatest benefit to the shareholders, moreover, such dividend payment shall be depended on the performance, financial position, financial liquidity and the necessity of capital flow in business administration, and the Company&#039;s business expansion, including economics situation.
    </td>
  </tr>
